":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"MALINES","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Juan, Erasmo, Ignacio, Luis, Ricardo, Roberto, Rosendo, Alejandro, Alicia, Amador, Ambrosio.","Catalan and Asturian-Leonese: habitational name from any of several towns called Marines, in Valencia and Asturias (Spain)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Floris","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: from a personal name derived from Latin <i>flos</i>, genitive <i>floris</i> ‘flower’.","Italian (Sardinia): plural form of   Flore  .","Greek: derivative of   Floros  , or a shortened form of any of various patronymics derived from this name, such as <b>Florakis</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Flore","meanings":["Name borne in Roman mythology by the goddess of flowers and the spring (a derivative of Latin <i>flos</i> ‘flower’, genitive <i>floris</i>). It is also the feminine form of the old Roman family name <i>Florus</i>, likewise derived from <i>flos</i>. <i>Flora</i> was little used in England before the 18th century, when it was imported from Scotland. In  1746   Flora Macdonald  (  1722–90 ) of Milton in South Uist helped Bonnie Prince Charlie to escape from there to the Island of Skye, disguised as a woman, after his defeat at Culloden. In fact, <i>Flora</i> was merely an Anglicized form of her Gaelic name, <i>Fionnaghal</i>, a variant of <i>Fionnguala</i> (  see  Fionnuala   ). However, her fame made the name <i>Flora</i> popular in the Highlands and elsewhere."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Floris BERTHOUT DE MALINES was born in 1250, in France, his father, Gauthier Walter VII BERTHOUT de MALINES de MECHELEN, was 26 and his mother, Marie d'Auvergne, was 26. He had at least 1 daughter with Mechtild van der Mark. He died in 1331, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1250–1331":"1250–1331","1255–1306":"1255–1306","1255–Male":"1255–Surnud","1270–1316":"1270–1316","1256–1307":"1256–1307","–Male":"Surnud","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1225–1288":"1225–1288","1225–1280":"1225–1280","2 JUN 1280":"2. juuni 1280","1250":"1250","23 JUN 1288":"23. juuni 1288","18 DEC 1238":"18. detsember 1238","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1225":"1225","1256":"1256","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1331":"1331","6 May 1329":"6. mai 1329","1307":"1307","1329":"1329","1306":"1306","Kleve, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Kleve, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Louvain,,Brabant Flamand,Flandre,Belgique,":"Leuven, Vlaams-Brabant, Belgia","Malines, Anvers, Flandre, Belgique":"Mechelen, Antwerpen, Belgia","France":"Prantsusmaa","Cologne,50769,,Rhénanie-du-Nord-Westphalie,ALLEMAGNE,Worringen":"Worringen, Köln, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksamaa","Mechelen, Antwerpen, België":"Mechelen, Antwerpen, Belgia"},"fi":{"1250–1331":"1250–1331","1255–1306":"1255–1306","1255–Male":"1255–Kuollut","1270–1316":"1270–1316","1256–1307":"1256–1307","–Male":"Kuollut","1290–1329":"1290–1329","1225–1288":"1225–1288","1225–1280":"1225–1280","2 JUN 1280":"2. kesäkuuta 1280","1250":"1250","23 JUN 1288":"23. kesäkuuta 1288","18 DEC 1238":"18. joulukuuta 1238","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","1290":"1290","1316":"1316","1225":"1225","1256":"1256","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1331":"1331","6 May 1329":"6. toukokuuta 1329","1307":"1307","1329":"1329","1306":"1306","Kleve, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Duitsland":"Kleve, Nordrhein-Westfalen, Saksa","Louvain,,Brabant Flamand,Flandre,Belgique,":"Leuven, Vlaams-Brabant, Belgia","Malines, Anvers, Flandre, Belgique":"Mechelen, Antwerpen, Belgia"